Raman Spectral Dataset of p53 Variants on Plasmonic/Metallic Substrates


This dataset contains Raman spectra acquired from three variants of the p53 protein:

* Wild-type (WT)
* R175H mutant
* R273H mutant

Measurements were performed using four different substrates:

* Aluminum (Al)
* AgNP@Al (Silver nanoparticles on Aluminum)
* AuNR@Al (Gold nanorods on Aluminum)
* AuNS@Al (Gold nanospheres on Aluminum)

The objective of the dataset is to compare spectral signatures of p53 variants and evaluate the effect of substrate-enhanced Raman configurations.


---Dataset Structure---

The table below summarizes the number of acquisition lines and total spectra collected for each condition.

| p53 Type  | Aluminum | AgNP@Al | AuNR@Al | AuNS@Al |
| --------- | -------- | ------- | ------- | ------- |
| Wild-type | 14 (626) | 5 (150) | 5 (150) | 6 (170) |
| R175H     | 8 (325)  | 5 (150) | 6 (200) | 6 (200) |
| R273H     | 11 (480) | 3 (121) | 3 (150) | 4 (200) |



Protein Variants

* Wild-type p53: native conformation reference.
* R175H: structural mutant commonly associated with conformational destabilization.
* R273H: DNA-contact mutant affecting binding activity.

Substrates

* Aluminum: non-plasmonic metallic reference substrate.
* AgNP@Al: aluminum coated/decorated with silver nanoparticles.
* AuNR@Al: aluminum decorated with gold nanorods.
* AuNS@Al: aluminum decorated with gold nanospheres.


This dataset may be used for:

* Raman spectral comparison of protein variants
* Surface-enhanced Raman spectroscopy (SERS) studies
* Biomolecular conformational analysis
* Machine learning classification of protein mutations
* PCA, LDA, SVM, Random Forest, Neural Networks
* Substrate performance benchmarking



